    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Dioscorea hyalinomarginata are saponins, diosbulbin B, diosbulbin C, diosgenin and dioscin. Diosbulbin B and diosbulbin C have been shown to possess anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial properties, with diosbulbin C exhibiting the most significant inhibitory activity against inflammatory mediators. Diosgenin, a steroid saponin, has been reported to have anti-inflammatory and antioxidant effects, as well as the ability to induce apoptosis in cancer cells. Dioscin, a glycoside saponin, has been demonstrated to possess anti-inflammatory and antipyretic properties, and has been used to treat fever and rheumatism. The saponins in Dioscorea hyalinomarginata are responsible for its medicinal properties, with diosbulbin B, diosbulbin C, diosgenin and dioscin contributing to its anti-inflammatory, antimicrobial and antioxidant effects.",
