    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Dioscorea hyalinomarginata are dioscorea tea, dioscorea decoction, dioscorea tincture, dioscorea extract, and dioscorea capsules. Dioscorea tea is made by steeping the dried tuber in hot water to create a decoction rich in diosgenin and other bioactive compounds. Dioscorea decoction is a concentrated liquid preparation made by boiling the dried tuber in water, often used to enhance the bioavailability of its active constituents. Dioscorea tincture is a concentrated liquid extract obtained by macerating the dried tuber in a solvent such as ethanol, commonly used in traditional medicine to treat various health conditions. Dioscorea extract is a powdered or liquid concentrate obtained through solvent extraction methods, often standardized to contain a specific amount of diosgenin and other bioactive compounds.",
